<span id="freeTextContainer11350032778917725494">Parts of this book are wonderful, and the middle aged Betta who has just lost her husband, is very endearing at times. At others I found Betta hard to relate to, her husband is described in such glowing terms, and the memories are all of such wonderful thoughtfulness and romance on his part--he just didn&apos;t ring true for me. I did like her ability to reconnect with old friends, and to try to rebuild her life.</span>
