<div id="review_3788344453" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3788344453" />
    <a title="Rhuddem Gwelin" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/85683243-rhuddem-gwelin"><img alt="Rhuddem Gwelin" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1563449062p2/85683243.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3788344453?book_show_action=true">Jan 23, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Rhuddem Gwelin" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Rhuddem Gwelin" href="/user/show/85683243-rhuddem-gwelin">Rhuddem Gwelin</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3788344453" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5700143366777852870">For the first hundred pages or so I just sighed and thought, oh yeah, another middle-aged widow with a perfect but dead husband who moves to a charming little town in Illinois with charming people and charming shops and she&apos;s going to open her own charming shop with her kooky friends. But I kept reading for some reason and became just slightly addicted, It&apos;s not really worth 3* but more than two. I&apos;ll probably even read more by her.</span>
  <span id="freeText5700143366777852870" style="display:none">For the first hundred pages or so I just sighed and thought, oh yeah, another middle-aged widow with a perfect but dead husband who moves to a charming little town in Illinois with charming people and charming shops and she's going to open her own charming shop with her kooky friends. But I kept reading for some reason and became just slightly addicted, It's not really worth 3* but more than two. I'll probably even read more by her.</span>
